# {{.Project}}

A sov mesh scaffold: one central registry gateway plus N pods, all
running under docker-compose.

## Quickstart

```sh
# Generate fresh HMAC + mesh secrets (already done by `sov init mesh`,
# re-run if you want to rotate).
sov init secrets

# Source secrets so docker-compose interpolates them.
set -a; . .sov.env; set +a

# Build + boot the mesh.
docker compose up --build

# Inspect what registered.
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/rpc/_introspect | jq

# Call the sample Echo handler.
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/rpc/Echo/echo \
  -H 'content-type: application/json' \
  -d '{"message":"hi"}'
```

## Layout

- `gateway/` — registry gateway (`sov.NewRegistry`).
- `pod/` — sample pod (`sov.NewPod` + `gw.RunMesh`).
- `Dockerfile` — multi-stage build, ROLE arg picks which cmd to build.
- `docker-compose.yml` — gateway + two pods.
- `.sov.env` — random HMAC + mesh secrets. **Do not commit.**

Add additional services by duplicating `pod/` and registering a new
router (rename `EchoRouter`).
